WEBVTT

00:03.137 --> 00:05.673
(CELLPHONE BEEPING)

00:05.706 --> 00:07.275
(CLICKS)

00:07.308 --> 00:09.643
**

00:15.383 --> 00:17.851
**

00:21.689 --> 00:24.658
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

00:24.692 --> 00:28.296
**

00:28.329 --> 00:29.697
(SIGHS)

00:29.730 --> 00:32.066
**

00:35.803 --> 00:38.172
**

00:41.842 --> 00:44.678
(SNIFFS, SIGHS)

00:44.712 --> 00:46.947
(FLORENCE + THE MACHINE'S
"KISS WITH A FIST" PLAYS)

00:46.980 --> 00:49.150
* You hit me once,
I hit you back

00:49.183 --> 00:51.319
* You gave a kick,
I gave a slap

00:51.352 --> 00:53.721
* You smashed a plate
over my head

00:53.754 --> 00:57.891
* Then I set fire to our bed

00:57.925 --> 01:00.528
* Oh, oh

01:00.561 --> 01:02.830
* My black eye casts no shadow

01:02.863 --> 01:05.032
* Your red eye sees nothing

01:05.065 --> 01:07.268
* Your slaps don't stick,
your kicks don't hit

01:07.301 --> 01:09.103
* So we remain the same

01:09.137 --> 01:11.305
* Love sticks, sweat drips
(GRUNTING)

01:11.339 --> 01:13.507
* Break the lock
if it don't fit

01:13.541 --> 01:15.509
* A kick in the teeth
is good for some

01:15.543 --> 01:18.112
* A kiss with a fist
is better than none

01:19.947 --> 01:22.183
* Whoa-oh

01:22.216 --> 01:26.954
* A kiss with a fist
is better than none

01:26.987 --> 01:29.190
* I broke your jaw once before

01:29.223 --> 01:31.058
* I spilled your blood
upon the floor

01:31.091 --> 01:32.526
* You broke
my leg in retur... *

01:32.560 --> 01:33.594
(SCREAMS)

01:33.627 --> 01:36.029
Holy crap, Shaun!

01:36.063 --> 01:38.232
(SIGHS)
You're a good dancer.

01:38.266 --> 01:42.069
No, I'm not.
So don't be a lurker.

01:42.102 --> 01:43.871
You've gotta
give a girl a warning

01:43.904 --> 01:46.039
before she makes a total fool
out of herself.

01:46.073 --> 01:47.241
I'm sorry.

01:47.275 --> 01:50.244
Why are you even up?
You've just gone through hell.

01:50.278 --> 01:52.045
You should be
sleeping till noon,

01:52.079 --> 01:55.283
then go out for
a Bloody Mary Brunch

01:55.316 --> 01:57.351
and a credit crashing
shopping spree.

01:57.385 --> 02:00.754
Those are all unhealthy ways
to cope with stress.

02:00.788 --> 02:02.256
(SIGHS) Fine.

02:02.290 --> 02:06.059
But whatever you choose to do
to decompress on your day off,

02:06.093 --> 02:07.861
it can't start
before 9:00.

02:07.895 --> 02:10.264
And it absolutely
cannot involve

02:10.298 --> 02:13.066
you sitting around all day
reading medical journals.

02:13.100 --> 02:16.036
You've got to get out
and do something.

02:16.069 --> 02:18.306
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

02:20.441 --> 02:22.210
I'm so sorry
for pushing you.

02:22.243 --> 02:23.777
But you know
I am right.

02:24.978 --> 02:25.979
Ooh.

02:27.281 --> 02:29.283
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

02:30.418 --> 02:32.486
**

02:37.325 --> 02:39.360
**

02:44.265 --> 02:46.434
**

02:51.439 --> 02:53.574
DR ANDREWS: How can you
investigate a response

02:53.607 --> 02:54.775
that's not even over yet?

02:54.808 --> 02:56.410
We just began
the Terminal Clean.

02:56.444 --> 02:59.012
The Governor believes
an immediate D.I.S. review

02:59.046 --> 03:01.415
is essential to restore
public confidence.

03:01.449 --> 03:04.952
The CDC confirmed the virus
originated in Malaysia.

03:04.985 --> 03:06.754
And that there was nothing
my staff could've done

03:06.787 --> 03:09.690
to prevent the three deaths
or Dr. Lim's infection.

03:10.691 --> 03:13.093
I'm going to need access
to every patient record

03:13.126 --> 03:15.263
and all staff communication

03:15.296 --> 03:17.498
from the moment the first
outbreak patient arrived.

03:17.865 --> 03:20.067
**

03:25.573 --> 03:27.675
**

03:33.547 --> 03:36.116
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

03:36.149 --> 03:38.319
**

03:43.591 --> 03:45.926
**

03:51.064 --> 03:53.367
Look at you.
Already back at work.

03:54.768 --> 03:57.170
It's either that
or watch the news.

03:57.204 --> 04:00.341
And I'd rather be back on ECMO
with a rusty cannula.

04:00.374 --> 04:02.743
Anything you need?
Thanks, but not necessary.

04:03.110 --> 04:04.712
You sure?

04:04.745 --> 04:07.481
Magazines, a book,
a Maple Bacon doughnut?

04:07.515 --> 04:09.883
Yeah, you don't have to play
"supportive friend"

04:09.917 --> 04:12.152
just because
we slept together.

04:12.185 --> 04:14.888
I'm not "playing,"
I'm being nice.

04:14.922 --> 04:16.490
(KEYS CLACKING)

04:16.524 --> 04:18.091
Which I've done for people
I haven't slept with

04:18.125 --> 04:20.160
many times in my life.

04:20.193 --> 04:21.762
No doubt.

04:21.795 --> 04:24.365
But until we did,
you were always
more interested

04:24.398 --> 04:27.200
in competing than supporting.

04:27.234 --> 04:28.869
And that's
how I prefer it.

04:30.270 --> 04:31.505
Okay.

04:31.539 --> 04:33.707
I'm not sure that's true,
or fair...

04:33.741 --> 04:37.778
I'm also exhausted,
unshowered, and constipated,

04:37.811 --> 04:40.180
so if you could shut the door
on your way out,

04:40.213 --> 04:41.582
I'd really appreciate it.

04:41.615 --> 04:42.750
(MONITOR BEEPING)

04:45.786 --> 04:47.054
Will do.

04:55.663 --> 04:57.230
* Wake up, Maggie

04:57.264 --> 05:02.169
* I think I got something
to say to you

05:03.671 --> 05:05.373
* It's late September

05:05.406 --> 05:09.777
* And I really should be
back at school

05:11.645 --> 05:14.448
* I know
I keep you amused... *

05:14.982 --> 05:17.017
(CELLPHONE VIBRATING)

05:21.655 --> 05:23.557
(BEEPS)

05:23.591 --> 05:25.325
Hello?
DR REZNICK:
You up for mimosas?

05:25.359 --> 05:27.327
I was just about to
head out to Hollander's,

05:27.361 --> 05:28.929
and I thought you
might want to join me.

05:28.962 --> 05:32.600
You thought I might
want to join you for mimosas?

05:32.633 --> 05:33.967
Why not?

05:34.001 --> 05:36.837
Because we don't
like each other?

05:36.870 --> 05:39.306
We don't really
know each other.

05:39.339 --> 05:42.109
Hollander's has the absolute
best brunch in San Jose.

05:42.142 --> 05:43.844
I'll drive. I'll buy.

05:43.877 --> 05:46.847
Morgan, how about you just cut
to what it is you really want.

05:46.880 --> 05:48.281
What else are
you gonna do?

05:48.315 --> 05:50.851
Sit around, play guitar,
and sing into your phone?

05:50.884 --> 05:53.454
How did you know
what I was doing?
I didn't.

05:53.487 --> 05:54.988
But that's
what your profile

05:55.022 --> 05:56.356
on a certain
dating app says

05:56.390 --> 05:59.192
you like to do
on your days off?
Are you stalking me?

05:59.226 --> 06:01.795
One mimosa and I'll tell you
the fake profile

06:01.829 --> 06:03.464
I use for "oppo research."

06:03.497 --> 06:06.600
The guy I used
for my pic is gorgeous.

06:06.634 --> 06:08.669
You really want to risk
swiping right on me?

06:11.004 --> 06:12.305
I'll drive myself.

06:12.339 --> 06:14.174
It'll be fun.
Meet you in an hour.

06:15.709 --> 06:17.511
Call me every night.

06:17.545 --> 06:18.946
(SIGHS)
I already said I would.

06:18.979 --> 06:20.481
Okay.
(CHUCKLES)

06:22.049 --> 06:23.517
Thanks for letting me
stop by.

06:23.551 --> 06:25.052
No problem.

06:25.486 --> 06:28.188
Okay, well...

06:29.557 --> 06:30.624
Bye.

06:30.658 --> 06:32.025
Bye.

06:32.059 --> 06:33.193
Bye.

06:33.761 --> 06:34.895
Okay.

06:37.164 --> 06:38.532
Bye.

06:38.566 --> 06:39.700
(SIGHS)

06:39.733 --> 06:41.168
(DOOR CLOSES)

06:43.771 --> 06:46.173
Mia, wait.

06:46.206 --> 06:48.842
Why don't you
stay and fly back
with Kellan on Sunday?

06:48.876 --> 06:51.044
I know it's crazy,
but it's been so long

06:51.078 --> 06:52.680
since we've
all been together.

06:52.713 --> 06:54.882
Like old times.

06:54.915 --> 06:57.250
I think that virus
may've affected your memory.

06:57.284 --> 06:59.753
(SCOFFS) Come on.
Hang with us a bit.

07:00.888 --> 07:02.890
Just take a break
for a few days.

07:02.923 --> 07:03.957
I'm sure you
could use one.

07:06.794 --> 07:08.562
It does sound nice.

07:09.396 --> 07:10.598
But I can't.

07:12.466 --> 07:13.701
Okay.

07:16.236 --> 07:17.638
Have a safe flight.

07:23.977 --> 07:25.879
But I could take
a later flight out tonight.

07:26.947 --> 07:27.948
Perfect.

07:33.120 --> 07:34.922
What are you doing?

07:35.789 --> 07:37.791
I am buttoning my shirt.

07:37.825 --> 07:40.027
The procedure
was a success.

07:40.060 --> 07:43.396
The CSF leak was fixed.
What are you doing here?

07:43.430 --> 07:44.865
Thought this
was your day off.

07:44.898 --> 07:47.467
Lea said I'm not allowed
to read medical journals,

07:47.501 --> 07:51.238
and Dr. Blaize said you can't
be discharged for two days.

07:51.271 --> 07:53.541
Ah, yes, and yet
the U.S. Constitution

07:53.574 --> 07:55.643
says I can leave
whenever I want.

07:55.676 --> 07:57.711
I am sick and tired
of being sick.

07:57.745 --> 07:59.713
I'm sick and tired of being
around sick people.

07:59.747 --> 08:04.317
Surgery and radiation
and blood draws,

08:04.351 --> 08:06.554
CT's, MRIs...

08:06.587 --> 08:08.321
I've had it.
I need a break.

08:08.355 --> 08:09.990
If you delay
the chemotherapy,

08:10.023 --> 08:11.759
you will weaken
its effectiveness.

08:11.792 --> 08:12.826
It'll be fine.

08:12.860 --> 08:14.628
Y-You can't quit.

08:14.662 --> 08:16.697
I'm not quitting, Shaun!

08:17.531 --> 08:18.932
I'm just...

08:18.966 --> 08:21.802
(SIGHS)

08:21.835 --> 08:24.972
I appreciate your concern,
but you just have no idea.

08:25.005 --> 08:26.940
No, it hasn't
had time to heal.

08:26.974 --> 08:29.577
If it leaks,
it would be bad.

08:29.610 --> 08:31.979
You could develop
a subdural hematoma...

08:32.012 --> 08:34.948
And yet if I stay one more
minute in this place,

08:34.982 --> 08:36.617
I will lose my mind.

08:37.384 --> 08:39.519
**

08:49.329 --> 08:52.299
**

08:52.332 --> 08:53.500
Where are you going?

08:53.533 --> 08:55.368
Anywhere I don't
smell iodoform.

08:55.402 --> 08:57.170
I'm coming with you.
You don't have to
come with me.

08:57.204 --> 08:59.139
I don't like
that smell either.

09:00.540 --> 09:02.142
But where are we going?

09:02.876 --> 09:04.177
Are we friends?

09:04.978 --> 09:06.546
Yes.
Why?

09:06.580 --> 09:07.748
'Cause I helped you
through school,

09:07.781 --> 09:09.683
because I helped
you get a job?

09:09.717 --> 09:12.920
Or is it because neither one
of us have any other friends?

09:12.953 --> 09:15.322
You have lots of friends.
Who?

09:15.355 --> 09:18.158
And if I did, why did I have
somebody drive me around

09:18.191 --> 09:21.729
who I barely know and who
I don't really like very much?

09:21.762 --> 09:23.997
And by the way, why doesn't
she have any other friends

09:24.031 --> 09:25.032
besides you?

09:26.600 --> 09:27.768
She does.

09:27.801 --> 09:31.204
She goes out with people
all the time.

09:31.238 --> 09:33.807
And yet she slept
on your floor for a month.
(CELLPHONE RINGING)

09:33.841 --> 09:36.176
So unless the people she goes
out with are homeless...

09:36.209 --> 09:37.377
Hello, Lea.

09:37.410 --> 09:38.746
LEA:
You better not be studying.

09:38.779 --> 09:40.480
I'm not.
Good.

09:40.513 --> 09:41.949
You want to come
have lunch with me?

09:42.950 --> 09:45.052
Lea wants us
to have lunch with her.

09:45.085 --> 09:46.720
Wait, us?
Who are you with?

09:46.754 --> 09:47.921
SHAUN:
Dr. Glassman.

09:48.689 --> 09:50.924
Fine.
Glassy can come, too.

09:50.958 --> 09:53.060
Glassy never said
he wanted to come.

09:53.093 --> 09:55.128
Tell him the food
at my office
is amazing.

09:55.528 --> 09:56.697
Okay.

09:56.730 --> 09:58.932
She says that
the food at her...
I'm not hungry!

09:58.966 --> 10:00.768
Go. You just go.

10:00.801 --> 10:02.369
(SIREN WAILS IN DISTANCE)

10:04.972 --> 10:06.573
I can't come.

10:06.606 --> 10:08.742
Come on, Shaun. Please?

10:08.776 --> 10:10.543
I'm having
a really crappy day,

10:10.577 --> 10:12.479
and you're, like,
my only friend.

10:16.416 --> 10:18.485
You know what?
I changed my mind.

10:19.687 --> 10:22.589
I would love to come and have
lunch with your friend Lea.

10:22.622 --> 10:23.691
Yes!

10:23.724 --> 10:25.292
Okay, I will text you guys
the address.

10:25.793 --> 10:27.427
(CLICKS)

10:32.833 --> 10:34.034
(SIGHS)

10:34.067 --> 10:35.669
Diego Luis.

10:36.770 --> 10:38.171
My pseudonym.

10:38.205 --> 10:41.141
I think Latin names
are sexy.

10:41.174 --> 10:42.642
You might
want to pace yourself.

10:42.676 --> 10:44.344
We don't even
have the menu yet.

10:44.845 --> 10:46.313
I'll be fine.

10:47.948 --> 10:51.284
I'm really sorry
about that EMT.

10:51.318 --> 10:52.485
Tyler, right?

10:52.519 --> 10:54.521
I heard you guys
were kinda close.

10:55.689 --> 10:57.758
Well, you heard wrong.
I barely even knew him.

10:57.791 --> 10:59.092
Okay.

10:59.126 --> 11:01.261
But as long as I'm here.
If you want to talk about...

11:01.294 --> 11:03.731
I don't.
I wanted a brunch partner.

11:03.764 --> 11:04.998
Not a shrink.

11:05.032 --> 11:06.599
I'm not trying to
be a shrink.

11:06.633 --> 11:08.869
I'm trying to be
a decent human being.

11:10.971 --> 11:12.505
Of course you are.

11:12.539 --> 11:13.907
St. Claire to the rescue.

11:13.941 --> 11:15.575
What is your problem?

11:15.608 --> 11:17.610
You literally
blackmailed me to be here,

11:17.644 --> 11:19.412
and now you have the nerve
to act like I am the one...

11:19.446 --> 11:21.314
(CELLPHONE VIBRATING)

11:22.382 --> 11:24.284
(SIGHS)

11:25.152 --> 11:26.353
I'm gonna take
this outside.

11:26.386 --> 11:28.889
If you wanna
just get the check
that's fine with me.

11:31.291 --> 11:32.793
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

11:32.826 --> 11:34.427
Ho!
Yeah!

11:34.461 --> 11:35.628
Damn, I'm gonna
have to wear a helmet

11:35.662 --> 11:36.797
next time I pitch to you.

11:38.999 --> 11:40.667
Yeah!
There you go.

11:41.501 --> 11:42.502
(BATS CLINKING)

11:44.738 --> 11:46.139
You seeing anyone?

11:48.408 --> 11:50.210
Sorry, don't mean
to interrogate.

11:50.243 --> 11:53.146
It's all right.
And no, I'm not.

11:53.180 --> 11:54.181
What about you?

11:54.915 --> 11:56.716
Yeah,
but it's nothing serious.

11:56.750 --> 11:58.118
It's okay if it is.

11:58.151 --> 11:59.486
I'd tell you if it was.

11:59.519 --> 12:01.288
You don't have to
tell me anything.

12:01.321 --> 12:02.322
It's none of my business.

12:05.325 --> 12:07.394
Could you imagine us
ever getting back together?

12:08.395 --> 12:09.729
Yeah, sure.

12:09.763 --> 12:12.132
I mean, the same way
I can imagine what it's like

12:12.165 --> 12:14.234
to walk across hot coals

12:14.267 --> 12:17.470
or to be waterboarded
or attacked by
a great white...

12:17.504 --> 12:19.206
All right, I get it.
Very funny.

12:24.845 --> 12:26.914
**

12:33.120 --> 12:35.155
Dr. Andrews,
can I help you?

12:35.188 --> 12:37.925
I just wanted to make sure you
have everything you need.

12:37.958 --> 12:39.692
Yes, we do.
Thank you.

12:39.726 --> 12:42.329
Any update?
Anything I should know?

12:42.362 --> 12:45.065
It's best if we wait until
the investigation is complete

12:45.098 --> 12:47.034
before discussing
any findings.

12:47.067 --> 12:48.568
You already
have findings?

12:48.601 --> 12:50.938
None that I'm prepared
to discuss.
Okay.

12:50.971 --> 12:53.006
Although, I was a bit
surprised to learn

12:53.040 --> 12:54.975
that you have a part-time
Chief of Surgery.

12:57.744 --> 13:00.447
What're you talking about?
I was here around the clock.

13:00.480 --> 13:02.115
In your role
as Chief of Surgery

13:02.149 --> 13:04.317
or as the hospital's
President?

13:06.153 --> 13:08.555
My dual role
was a benefit.

13:08.588 --> 13:09.756
It sped up
decision-making

13:09.789 --> 13:11.758
and ensured that
there was no miscommunication

13:11.791 --> 13:14.394
between administration
and the surgical staff.

13:15.929 --> 13:19.099
Not to mention
this is none of your business.

13:19.132 --> 13:21.869
D.P.H. has no oversight
of our management structure.

13:21.902 --> 13:24.137
If it adversely affects
patient care...

13:24.171 --> 13:27.807
Oh, it didn't.
And it never has.

13:29.609 --> 13:31.144
(SCOFFS)

13:31.178 --> 13:34.014
You bureaucrats
have no idea

13:34.047 --> 13:37.117
how a hospital runs
or what doctors and nurses

13:37.150 --> 13:38.986
have to do
on a daily basis

13:39.019 --> 13:41.955
to provide optimum care
for patients.

13:41.989 --> 13:43.957
And you can tell that
to the Governor.

13:46.994 --> 13:48.929
I have to go.
Mimosas. Plural.

13:48.962 --> 13:50.130
That was the deal.

13:50.163 --> 13:51.932
I've had one.
You've had one quarter.

13:51.965 --> 13:54.301
Yeah, well,
my mom is getting evicted.

13:55.168 --> 13:57.237
Fine.
I'll come along.

13:57.270 --> 13:58.972
I'm not lying.
I have to help her move.

13:59.006 --> 14:00.974
I could use the exercise.
No.

14:01.008 --> 14:03.443
Two cars are better than one.
Stop.

14:03.476 --> 14:04.844
What is going on?

14:09.116 --> 14:10.150
You were right.

14:11.484 --> 14:15.889
Tyler's death was...
upsetting.

14:17.925 --> 14:22.129
I can carry a lot.
And I'm great with moms.

14:24.864 --> 14:25.865
Okay.

14:28.501 --> 14:31.404
She doesn't think
I can be both President
and Chief of Surgery.

14:31.838 --> 14:32.839
Really?

14:34.407 --> 14:35.642
You agree with her?

14:38.678 --> 14:40.447
I never was a fan
of your staying on

14:40.480 --> 14:42.515
as Chief
after your promotion.

14:42.549 --> 14:44.217
You really think anything
would've been different

14:44.251 --> 14:46.086
if someone else was Chief
during the outbreak?

14:46.119 --> 14:49.122
You used to have more time
to manage scheduling issues.

14:49.156 --> 14:51.891
And staffing shortage
did complicate our response.

14:51.925 --> 14:55.028
Every hospital in this country
is facing a nursing shortage.

14:56.229 --> 14:58.198
I'm not gonna reverse
my decision now.

14:58.231 --> 14:59.699
I'd look like
an indecisive fool.

15:00.934 --> 15:02.502
Or like someone
who's realized

15:02.535 --> 15:05.538
they've made a mistake
and reconsidered.

15:09.442 --> 15:10.643
Welcome.

15:10.677 --> 15:12.479
(SIGHS) Wow.

15:12.512 --> 15:14.381
How are you not
all 300 pounds?

15:14.414 --> 15:16.383
We also have
an amazing gym,

15:16.416 --> 15:18.385
a basketball court,
and an ice rink.

15:18.418 --> 15:20.187
You have
a very generous boss.

15:20.220 --> 15:21.521
And idiot investors.

15:21.554 --> 15:23.156
The founder's
from Minnesota.

15:23.190 --> 15:25.092
He's obsessed with hockey,
so there's pickup at lunch

15:25.125 --> 15:26.759
and a beer league
after work.

15:26.793 --> 15:29.562
No Flying Glass Elevators?
Get anything you want.

15:29.596 --> 15:31.164
There's also a pasta bar

15:31.198 --> 15:34.334
and a deli and Spanish tapas
next door.

15:34.367 --> 15:37.437
And then we'll meet back out
in the atrium for our feast.

15:37.470 --> 15:39.806
Any of your co-workers
gonna be joining us?

15:41.774 --> 15:42.842
Why?

15:42.875 --> 15:44.877
I don't know.
Just trying to be social.

15:47.347 --> 15:49.716
You didn't want to come,
then you did.

15:49.749 --> 15:50.750
What changed?

15:51.551 --> 15:53.286
She always
this suspicious?

15:53.320 --> 15:56.723
(CHUCKLES)
I'm in the mood for Thai.

15:56.756 --> 15:58.091
Shaun?
No, thank you.

15:58.125 --> 15:59.892
Sherlock?
No.

15:59.926 --> 16:02.129
Okay, so I'll see you two
in a few.

16:02.162 --> 16:05.498
By the way, the lobster rolls
are amazing.

16:05.532 --> 16:07.934
Thank you.

16:07.967 --> 16:09.569
(MUTTERS)

16:09.602 --> 16:11.971
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

16:16.676 --> 16:18.611
Since when do
you eat bratwurst?

16:18.645 --> 16:21.581
Oh, thought I'd try
something new.

16:23.350 --> 16:25.952
You a Bulls fan, Breeze?
Bulls?

16:25.985 --> 16:29.089
Oh, no, that's from when
I played South by Southwest

16:29.122 --> 16:31.224
with Danny Attie's band.

16:31.258 --> 16:34.294
That was Austin.
The Bulls are from Chicago.

16:38.831 --> 16:42.602
Mom, who else
is living here?

16:42.635 --> 16:44.937
It's someone else's mug,
but he is not living here.

16:44.971 --> 16:46.939
He just dropped you off
after a date

16:46.973 --> 16:49.476
and left his coffee mug
and bratwurst behind
by mistake?

16:49.509 --> 16:50.977
What do you guys care?

16:51.010 --> 16:53.346
Okay, I am not a child.
It's my damn apartment.

16:53.380 --> 16:54.481
Yeah, and it was my money

16:54.514 --> 16:57.684
that was supposed to
be paying for it.

16:57.717 --> 16:59.286
What was it this time?

16:59.319 --> 17:01.454
You guys were gonna start
a new record label?

17:01.488 --> 17:03.156
A restaurant? What?

17:03.190 --> 17:05.592
I didn't rip you off.
And he didn't rip me off.

17:05.625 --> 17:08.195
I was just
a little late.

17:08.228 --> 17:10.029
So you're getting evicted
because your landlord

17:10.063 --> 17:11.664
is a stickler
for prompt payments.

17:11.698 --> 17:13.300
It's the truth.

17:13.333 --> 17:16.703
Mom, why the hell
do you have to
get out of here so fast?

17:16.736 --> 17:19.038
There is no way it's because
of a mean landlord.

17:23.710 --> 17:26.246
Because he beat my ass,

17:26.279 --> 17:28.848
and I'm terrified
that he's gonna do it again.

17:28.881 --> 17:30.917
**

17:36.456 --> 17:38.258
And I'm not
going to the cops.

17:38.291 --> 17:40.493
I just want to
get the hell out
of this apartment

17:40.527 --> 17:42.329
and never come back.
That's it.

17:45.031 --> 17:46.966
Nananana-nananana-
nananana-nananana,

17:46.999 --> 17:49.236
nananana-nananana-
nananana-nananana.

17:49.269 --> 17:52.672
Putting's
all about process.

17:54.407 --> 17:56.309
(GROANS)

17:56.343 --> 17:58.378
Apparently not.

17:58.411 --> 18:01.581
Front nine's for posers.
Back nine's for closers.

18:01.614 --> 18:03.683
You just know
I hate that movie,

18:03.716 --> 18:05.252
and you're trying to
get me off my game.

18:05.285 --> 18:06.386
(CHUCKLES)

18:08.054 --> 18:09.556
But it's not gonna work.
(LAUGHS)

18:10.590 --> 18:11.724
Nice.

18:13.326 --> 18:14.894
So, what's she do?

18:14.927 --> 18:16.696
This woman you're
not serious about?

18:16.729 --> 18:18.698
(SIGHS)

18:18.731 --> 18:21.334
Come on.
You started it.

18:21.368 --> 18:23.903
And it was a mistake.

18:23.936 --> 18:26.306
All right,
what about work?

18:26.339 --> 18:29.542
Kellan said one of the other
residents has autism?

18:29.576 --> 18:31.944
Yeah. Dr. Murphy.

18:33.446 --> 18:35.415
So what's he like?

18:35.448 --> 18:38.951
He's a bit immature.
But nice.

18:40.253 --> 18:43.122
Wow, I feel like
I totally know him now.

18:44.891 --> 18:47.594
Sorry, I just don't
want to talk about work.

18:47.627 --> 18:49.429
Or your personal life.

18:49.462 --> 18:52.031
But I would like to
talk about something

18:52.064 --> 18:54.901
other than
your putting process.

18:57.003 --> 18:59.939
What's going on in your life?
How are you doing?

18:59.972 --> 19:01.674
I'm doing great.
Everything's fine.

19:03.743 --> 19:04.977
Come on, Mia.
I'm just trying to relax.

19:05.011 --> 19:06.012
Have some fun.

19:07.914 --> 19:10.082
This is exactly
why we broke up.

19:11.851 --> 19:13.920
That's not how
I remember it.

19:17.089 --> 19:18.925
I made a mistake.

19:18.958 --> 19:20.893
But we were broken
long before that.

19:20.927 --> 19:22.695
'Cause I didn't like
to talk about work?

19:24.030 --> 19:27.400
You decided to
leave the police force
and become a doctor,

19:27.434 --> 19:28.601
and the first
I heard of it

19:28.635 --> 19:30.470
is when you told me
you got into med school.

19:30.503 --> 19:32.472
Most people would think
that's a step up.

19:32.505 --> 19:33.606
Be supportive.

19:33.640 --> 19:36.243
How could I support
a man I never saw?

19:36.276 --> 19:38.645
And when I did see you,
we didn't talk.

19:38.678 --> 19:41.080
It's like everything
in your life

19:41.113 --> 19:43.650
can only be divulged
on a "need to know" basis.

19:43.683 --> 19:45.017
And I never
needed to know.

19:47.854 --> 19:49.689
Found this
in the trash.

19:49.722 --> 19:51.624
An old pay stub
for Carnell Hunter.

19:51.658 --> 19:54.627
I say we pay him a visit.
And do what?

19:54.661 --> 19:57.830
Give him a stern lecture
that'll teach him
to respect women?

19:57.864 --> 20:00.267
We need to make it clear
that abusing, stalking,

20:00.300 --> 20:02.402
or in any way bothering
your mom ever again

20:02.435 --> 20:04.136
will be more trouble
than it's worth.

20:04.170 --> 20:06.138
You're a bit out
of your element here.

20:06.172 --> 20:09.509
We're not dealing with some
frat boy or creepy surgeon.

20:09.542 --> 20:13.079
The guys my mom dates
are psychos.

20:14.514 --> 20:16.949
So you just
want to do nothing?
Let him get away with it?

20:16.983 --> 20:18.385
Is she doesn't
want to involve the police,

20:18.418 --> 20:19.819
there's nothing
we can do about it.

20:19.852 --> 20:23.390
Let's just help her get out of
this mess and be done with it.

20:23.423 --> 20:27.026
No. I'm not as clueless
as you think.
(SIGHS)

20:27.059 --> 20:28.628
I had a stalker
in med school.

20:28.661 --> 20:30.463
The guy was scary.

20:30.497 --> 20:34.301
Which is why now I never
go anywhere without this.

20:34.334 --> 20:35.902
What the hell?

20:35.935 --> 20:38.237
Don't worry. It's legal.
I have a C.C.W.

20:39.205 --> 20:42.675
So what're you gonna do?
Pop a cap in his ass?

20:42.709 --> 20:45.678
No. We just need to
send him a message.

20:45.712 --> 20:47.480
And studies have shown
that men are more likely

20:47.514 --> 20:48.815
to be visual learners.

20:48.848 --> 20:50.617
**

20:56.689 --> 20:58.658
Give me your key.

20:58.691 --> 21:00.660
Why?
I want to lock this.

21:00.693 --> 21:02.295
We're leaving
the car together.

21:02.329 --> 21:04.497
How am I gonna get it?
Key.

21:04.531 --> 21:07.600
You're the one who insisted
the guy was so dangerous.
I'm sure he is.

21:07.634 --> 21:09.569
But you with a gun
is even more frightening.

21:12.104 --> 21:14.106
Here. Go ahead.

21:17.410 --> 21:19.746
How come you're St. Claire
with everyone but your mom?

21:19.779 --> 21:21.881
Stop calling me
St. Claire.

21:21.914 --> 21:24.183
And you don't
know my mom.

21:24.216 --> 21:26.218
I know it's not
her fault she's bipolar.

21:32.992 --> 21:36.763
(INDISTINCT TALKING OVER P.A.)

21:36.796 --> 21:38.030
Feeling any better?

21:38.064 --> 21:40.099
Actually, I am.

21:40.132 --> 21:42.969
Nothing like a good B.M.
to turn a frown upside down.

21:44.471 --> 21:47.073
I've been thinking about
what you said this morning.

21:47.106 --> 21:48.941
About how competitive
I always am.

21:51.478 --> 21:55.081
And the more I think about it,
the angrier I get.

21:55.114 --> 21:59.118
All I was trying to say...
I have been nothing
but professional with you.

21:59.151 --> 22:00.286
And for the record,
you're the one

22:00.319 --> 22:02.455
who invited me
out for drinks.

22:02.489 --> 22:04.724
You're the one who wanted to
go back to my apartment.

22:04.757 --> 22:06.493
And now you're the one
who's acting differently

22:06.526 --> 22:07.927
just because we had sex.

22:07.960 --> 22:10.229
You need to project more,
use your diaphragm

22:10.262 --> 22:11.864
if you really want
the entire hospital
to hear you.

22:14.467 --> 22:16.469
I definitely won't go
out of my way
to be nice to you again.

22:17.437 --> 22:19.205
(SCOFFS)

22:23.142 --> 22:24.544
He doesn't trust me.

22:24.577 --> 22:25.978
I mean, why?

22:26.012 --> 22:28.347
Is he that way
with everybody or just me?

22:28.381 --> 22:29.949
Can you help me
convince him

22:29.982 --> 22:32.151
to start his chemotherapy
on schedule?

22:32.184 --> 22:35.354
You want me to
convince a brain surgeon,
who doesn't like me,

22:35.388 --> 22:37.690
that I know the best way
to treat his tumor?

22:38.525 --> 22:40.326
Yes.

22:40.359 --> 22:42.695
Maybe just
be supportive, Shaun.

22:42.729 --> 22:44.030
He just wants some time.

22:44.063 --> 22:48.134
No. He doesn't have time.
You don't understand.

22:48.167 --> 22:49.769
Actually,
I do understand.

22:49.802 --> 22:52.639
And I'm getting
really tired of people
treating me like I don't.

22:52.672 --> 22:54.441
I know how you feel.

22:54.474 --> 22:56.208
Where's your food?

22:56.242 --> 22:58.344
Too many options.
I got confused.

22:58.377 --> 23:00.847
You find out why no one
wants to eat with me?

23:00.880 --> 23:02.715
Still snooping.

23:02.749 --> 23:04.651
Hmm.

23:04.684 --> 23:06.052
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

23:09.288 --> 23:10.623
Okay.

23:10.657 --> 23:13.693
We all need
to do something fun.

23:13.726 --> 23:16.128
(ARCADE NOISES)

23:16.162 --> 23:18.264
(SIGHS)

23:21.501 --> 23:23.536
Either of you
need a refill?

23:23.570 --> 23:25.304
No, thanks.

23:25.337 --> 23:26.573
I'm good.

23:26.606 --> 23:28.240
Neither do I.

23:30.677 --> 23:32.645
But I'm gonna
get one anyways.

23:32.679 --> 23:35.014
I'll be in the arcade
when you two are done

23:35.047 --> 23:36.616
with whatever
you need to deal with.

23:39.385 --> 23:41.454
Regretting
your invite now?

23:42.221 --> 23:44.423
No. It's just, um...

23:48.528 --> 23:51.063
Maybe we should think about
trying to get back together.

23:51.864 --> 23:53.500
Are you insane?

23:53.533 --> 23:55.702
We can't even spend half a day
together without a fight.

23:55.735 --> 23:58.605
Yeah, I'm sorry.
I do respect you.

24:00.272 --> 24:02.274
Which is exactly why
I need you back in my life.

24:03.275 --> 24:05.111
To remind me
who I can be.

24:07.547 --> 24:08.581
Come on, Alex.

24:08.615 --> 24:10.583
You've just been through
a traumatic experience.

24:10.617 --> 24:13.219
You're exhausted...
And lonely.

24:20.560 --> 24:21.928
But...

24:23.963 --> 24:25.131
I love you.

24:27.800 --> 24:30.169
Just tell me
what I need to do,
and I'll do it.

24:31.003 --> 24:33.272
**

24:35.808 --> 24:37.076
Thank you.

24:38.477 --> 24:41.013
I know how hard it is
for you to open up.

24:42.248 --> 24:43.516
I love you, too.

24:44.283 --> 24:46.285
**

24:48.855 --> 24:51.423
But I think it's best
if we just

24:51.457 --> 24:53.960
keep moving forward
with our lives.

24:54.293 --> 24:56.629
**

25:02.869 --> 25:04.937
**

25:11.243 --> 25:13.980
(CLATTERING)

25:14.480 --> 25:16.949
**

25:21.854 --> 25:23.656
Carnell Hunter?

25:23.690 --> 25:26.659
Yeah?
We need to talk.

25:26.693 --> 25:29.261
Yeah, well,
I need to do my job.

25:29.295 --> 25:33.132
So unless you got a badge,
I ain't interested.

25:33.165 --> 25:34.533
Time for a break.

25:34.567 --> 25:36.135
Because we need to
tell you something,

25:36.168 --> 25:38.470
and we want to make sure
you're listening.

25:38.504 --> 25:40.439
Well, I'd get out of my face
if I were you.

25:40.472 --> 25:42.742
Or what?
You gonna beat my ass?

25:43.375 --> 25:44.877
Who the hell are you?

25:44.911 --> 25:46.813
Breeze Browne
is my mom.

25:46.846 --> 25:48.347
She's moving out of
the apartment today.

25:48.380 --> 25:50.717
And she never
wants to see you again.

25:50.750 --> 25:52.619
What are you
talking about?

25:52.652 --> 25:55.154
You're a disgusting,
pathetically weak coward.

25:55.187 --> 25:56.555
You know it.
And every woman

25:56.589 --> 25:58.090
you've ever been with
knows it, too.

25:59.325 --> 26:01.560
I don't know what
you're talking about,

26:01.594 --> 26:03.930
but I would never
lay my hands on a woman.

26:03.963 --> 26:05.531
Especially Breeze.

26:05.564 --> 26:07.734
I mean, she's the best thing
that's ever happened to me.

26:07.767 --> 26:09.168
I love her.

26:09.201 --> 26:11.403
You guys all memorize
the same speech, don't you?

26:13.205 --> 26:15.107
Why do you think
I asked her to marry me?

26:19.045 --> 26:20.613
Oh, she didn't tell you?

26:22.548 --> 26:24.416
What did she tell you?

26:27.453 --> 26:29.221
You had no right
to butt in.

26:29.255 --> 26:31.257
The poor guy
was almost in tears.

26:31.290 --> 26:34.093
Which is exactly
why I couldn't
tell him to his face.

26:34.126 --> 26:36.829
He's just... He's so darn
sensitive about everything.

26:36.863 --> 26:38.364
CLAIRE: So you thought
disappearing into the night

26:38.397 --> 26:40.232
would make it
easier for him?

26:40.266 --> 26:42.735
I know, you're right.
It's just...

26:44.070 --> 26:45.537
(SIGHS)

26:46.238 --> 26:48.274
I don't
want to marry him.

26:48.307 --> 26:50.710
So tell him
you're not ready.

26:50.743 --> 26:52.779
You want to take
things slower.

26:53.312 --> 26:56.415
(SIGHS, SCOFFS)

26:56.448 --> 26:59.285
He's one of the sweetest men
I've ever met.

26:59.318 --> 27:01.253
So why are you
trying to ghost him?

27:01.821 --> 27:04.056
**

27:07.126 --> 27:08.394
I don't know.

27:08.427 --> 27:10.029
**

27:10.062 --> 27:11.330
Mom...

27:11.731 --> 27:14.701
**

27:14.734 --> 27:16.803
(SIGHS)

27:16.836 --> 27:20.239
**

27:20.272 --> 27:23.575
Dr. Andrews,
we have some findings.

27:23.609 --> 27:25.577
I'm excited to hear them.

27:25.611 --> 27:27.880
And I just wanted to say,
with regard
to the staffing issue...

27:27.914 --> 27:30.249
I wouldn't worry
about that anymore.

27:30.282 --> 27:34.420
Uh, Dr. Audrey Lim
non-consensually dosed a man

27:34.453 --> 27:36.823
